HEADWORD: aplacophoran
<hw>aplacophoran</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>one of the
<er>aplacophora</er>; a deep-water wormlike mollusk lacking calcareous
plates on the body but having fine limy spicules on the covering
mantle.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> solenogaster</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

